! Focus model

The palette is one popup with up to eight focusable sections, partitioned into two groups:

* ''pills group'' (top of the palette, visually stacked): ''preset'' (always present — trailing ''+'' pill is the save-as affordance even when no presets exist), ''visibility'' (only when ≥ 1 visibility rule active), ''filter'' (only when ≥ 1 filter active), ''view'' (only when ≥ 2 views declared), ''structure'' (always present when the active view declares any channels), ''leader'' (only when ≥ 1 leader is visible for the active view — see leader scoping below). (As of 0.0.118 the three standalone row-decoration ''lens'' chooser strips are gone — they're relocated into the Structure strip's view→channel tree, see below.) The structure strip has a ''two-stage'' interaction model: on focus it shows a ''compact'' summary row (view name, channel count + composition, view-scoped pills sort/entries/grouping); pressing ''Enter / Space / →'' expands it to the full stacked layout. Expanded, the ''view'' row leads with three lens choosers — ''Name'' / ''Icon'' / ''Note'' — editing the view's default decoration lens per slot (`l` toggles a slot ''lock''); each ''channel'' row (indented under the view) leads with its own three choosers overriding or inheriting the view default (showing ''(inherit view)'' / 🔒 cues), followed by the channel's primitive pills (roots/children/leaf/label + row decorations + entity-type). A lens chooser cycles its lenses on ↵/Space and clears on DEL; new lenses are created via ''Manage lenses''. Built-in channels (the synthetic ''entries'' channel auto-appended to tree views) render muted to flag their automatic nature. ''Esc'' from expanded collapses back to compact; ''Esc'' from compact refocuses input. The leader strip surfaces every visible leader as a ''[key] name'' pill — same activation as the typed-gesture path (key + idle), but discoverable without prior knowledge. Leaders may opt into per-view scope via ''`ca-leader-views`'' (empty = global).
* ''main group'': ''input'' (search box), ''menu'' (result list), ''detail'' (Ctrl-hold drawer below the menu, only when open), ''preview'' (right-column pane, only when an entry/action on the stack registered a ''`ca-preview-template`'').

The active section gets the browser-level focus and a visual cue; keyboard gestures route accordingly. ''Tab'' cycles within the current group; ''Shift-Tab'' jumps between groups, restoring the focus you last held in the group you're entering (the menu row you were on, the filter pill you were editing, etc.); it falls back to the bottom-most pill (entering pills) or input (returning to main) when that slot has since disappeared or was never visited. ''↑ / ↓'' inside the pill group walks vertically across rows — ↑ from input enters pills at the bottom-most row, ↓ from the bottom-most pill drops back into input. ''Esc'' walks the stack back one step keystroke-by-keystroke: in input or menu focus it pops the current stage at any depth > 1, and from a pill section it returns focus to input. At root depth, Esc-from-input closes the palette and Esc-from-menu refocuses input. ''Shift-Esc'' is the universal "I'm done" — closes from any focus and any depth in one keystroke. ''Type-ahead'': pressing any printable character (no Ctrl/Alt/Meta) while focus is on a pill strip, the menu, the detail drawer or the preview background — and no section gesture claimed it — refocuses the input and appends the character, so you can start filtering from anywhere without first Tabbing back.

! Hotkey

|!Key |!Section |!Action |
|''Ctrl-Space'' |any |Open the palette |
|''Tab'' |any |Cycle focus within the current group only: pills (preset → visibility → filter → view → structure → leader) or main (input → menu → details). Rows only join the cycle when active. |
|''Shift-Tab'' |any |Jump between the two groups, restoring the focus you last held in the target group. Falls back to the bottom-most active pill (entering pills) / input (returning to main) when that slot is gone or unvisited. |
|''Enter'' |input / menu / details |Fire the selected item and close the palette. ''Exception:'' in input focus, if the current text matches a known filter or visibility prefix with a non-empty argument, Enter commits that pill instead. |
|''Ctrl-Enter'' |any |Fire the selected item but keep the palette open. Shift-Enter is a silent alias for back-compat (removed in v0.3). |
|''Alt-Enter'' |input / menu / details |Fire the selected row's ''primary row-icon'' (e.g. the 🌐 glyph opens an external URL in a new tab). No-op when the row has no icons resolved. |
|''Ctrl-Alt-Enter'' |input / menu / details |Fire the row's primary icon's ''secondary'' action — e.g. the 🌐 glyph copies the URL to the clipboard. No-op when the icon declares no `ca-row-icon-alt-*` gesture. |
|''Ctrl-DEL / Ctrl-Backspace'' |any |Clear ''both'' constraint strips (filters + visibility) AND the active-preset marker in one step. |
|''Esc'' |input |Pop one stage (back). At root depth (nothing to pop), closes the palette. |
|''Shift-Esc'' |any |Close the palette directly from any focus and any depth, in one keystroke. |
|''↓'' |input |Step into the menu (only if results exist) |
|''↑'' |input |Enter the pill group at the bottom-most active pill row (no-op if no pills active) |
|''(typing)'' |input |Filter the current stage. When the text matches a filter prefix, the input picks up a blue underline ("↵ commit filter: …"); when it matches a visibility prefix, an orange underline ("↵ commit visibility: …"); when it matches a leader key, an amber underline — leader fires after 500ms idle, any keystroke cancels. |
|''Esc'' |any (in pick-mode) |Cancel pick-mode — return to prior view without committing a filter |
|''Esc'' |preset / visibility / filter / view / details |Return focus to the input (without closing) |
|''Esc'' |menu |Pop one stage (back). At root depth, refocuses input (since there's nothing to pop). Symmetric with ArrowLeft-in-menu. |
|''← / →'' |visibility / filter |Move focus between pills within the row (clamps at edges) |
|''← / →'' |view / preset |Move focus between pills ''and apply on landing'' — these are single-select strips, so navigating IS selecting (no Space/Enter needed; clamps at edges). On preset the trailing ''+'' save pill is skipped — it stays an explicit Enter/Space gesture. (Lens choosers now live in the Structure strip's view→channel tree and cycle on ↵/Space, not on ←/→ landing.) |
|''Enter / Space'' |lens slot |Apply the focused lens (←/→ also applies on landing). On the ''➕ New…'' pill: start authoring a new lens for this slot (filter editor with a live match-count → name → save). |
|''e'' |lens slot (focused lens) |Edit the focused lens — reopens its projection filter live (a user lens is overwritten in place; a shipped lens is saved as a new copy). |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |lens slot (focused lens) |Delete the focused lens via a confirm drill (shipped lenses refuse — press ''e'' to clone instead). To turn a slot ''off'' instead, ← to its ''(off)'' / ''(default)'' head pill. |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |view |Delete the focused view via a confirm drill (shipped views refuse — fork via ''Manage views'' instead). ''Manage views → Fork current view'' makes a fully independent persisted copy: the `ca-view-*` fields PLUS a private copy of every explicit channel and grouping axis the view references (titles rewritten), so editing the fork's structure never touches the original. The built-in entries channel is referenced, not copied. |

!! Editing a view's long-tail fields

The Structure strip edits a view's ''core structure'' (roots / children / leaf / label / axis chain) and enum facets (sort / include-entries / grouping) live, with preview. Everything else — the ''long tail'' — is edited from ''Manage views → Edit all fields…'', a drill that lists every remaining view-scoped field as an editable row, grouped:

* ''identity'' — `ca-view-name`, `ca-view-hint`, `ca-icon`, `ca-order`
* ''display'' — `ca-view-count-format` (text); `ca-view-show-count`, `ca-view-containers-first`, `ca-view-show-action-preview`, `ca-view-show-side-preview`, `ca-view-context-aware` (yes/no toggles)
* ''sort detail'' — `ca-view-sort-field`, `ca-view-sort-key`
* ''picking'' — `ca-view-pick-mode`, `ca-view-pick-emits-filter`, `ca-view-after-fire`
* ''row defaults'' — `ca-view-row-hint`, `ca-view-row-icon`, `ca-view-row-order`, `ca-view-row-next-scope`, `ca-view-row-items-from` (the per-row overrides not surfaced as Structure-strip pills)
* ''preview'' — `ca-view-preview`, `ca-view-preview-name`, `ca-view-preview-title` (the view-level Overview-row summary)
* ''channels'' — each explicit channel the view composes drills into its OWN field editor (name, `ca-channel-source`, `ca-channel-include-position`, the `ca-channel-row-*` defaults, and a ''preview'' group: `ca-channel-preview`, `ca-channel-preview-name`, `ca-channel-preview-title`)

User views edit in place; a ''shipped'' (shadow-only) view or channel is read-only here and offers fork-to-edit (view) or a Structure-strip hint (channel) instead — editing in place would write an override. `ca-position-<view-slug>` is NOT edited here: per-entry placement lives on each ''entry'' tiddler, not the view.

!! Editing entries & actions in-palette

''Manage entries'' and ''Manage actions'' (top-level menu) list every command entry / action with a ''+ New …'' creator and one drillable row each. Drilling a row opens its field editor (`cp-entry-edit-rows` / `cp-action-edit-rows`):

* ''Entry'' — identity (`ca-name`/`ca-icon`/`ca-hint`/`ca-order`), `ca-kind` (leaf | drill), leaf behaviour (`ca-actions`, `ca-after-fire`, `ca-confirm` + `ca-confirm-consequence`), and drill target (`ca-next-scope`, `ca-items-from`, `ca-next-title`, `ca-next-entity-type`). Per-view placement (`ca-position-<view-slug>`) is set by hand on the entry (it varies per view) — a note row points this out.
* ''Action'' — identity, the three discovery facets (`ca-entity-type` = catalogue match · `ca-applies` = filter match · `ca-action-when` = narrowing — see [[Dev Workflow|$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/dev-workflow]] §"Debugging action discovery"), and behaviour (`ca-actions`, `ca-after-fire`, `ca-confirm` + consequence).

Creating prompts for a name then saves a fresh definition under the plugin namespace with sane defaults (entry: `ca-kind: leaf`; action: empty `ca-applies`), reopening the list with the new row under ''Your …''. USER definitions edit in place; a ''shipped'' (shadow-only) one is clone-protected — ''📋 Clone to a custom … to edit'' copies it first (an in-place edit would write a shadow-masking override). Delete is confirm-gated (user definitions only).
|''↑ / ↓'' |preset / visibility / filter / view / leader |Walk between pill rows. ↓ at the bottom-most row drops into input; ↑ at the top-most row no-ops. |
|''Enter / Space'' |view |Activate the highlighted view — pops the stack to root, rebuilds the menu. (←/→ already applies on landing, so this is mostly redundant on the view strip.) |
|''Enter / Space'' |preset |Apply the focused preset (replaces filters + visibility, switches view, keeps palette open). The applied preset becomes the ''active'' preset until cleared. (←/→ also applies on landing; only the ''+'' pill still requires Enter/Space.) On the trailing ''+'' pill: open the save-as prompt to capture current state as a new preset (same as the `s` leader). |
|''Ctrl-Enter'' |preset |Overwrite the focused preset with the current state. Only effective when the focused pill IS the active preset AND it's dirty (current state diverges from the captured baseline). No-op on the ''+'' pill. |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |preset |Push a confirm-drill to permanently delete the focused preset tiddler. Confirm with Enter, cancel with Esc. No-op on the ''+'' pill. |
|''Home / End'' |preset |Jump focus to the first preset / to the ''+'' save pill (last position) |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |filter / visibility |Remove the focused pill |
|''Enter'' |filter / visibility |Move focus into the detail pane to scroll through the full help text |
|''↵ / Space / →'' |structure (compact) |Expand the strip to the full per-channel layout (first pill focused) |
|''↑ / ↓'' |structure (compact) |Walk to adjacent pill section (up = previous, down = next or input) |
|''← / →'' |structure (expanded) |Move focus between pills within the current sub-row |
|''↑ / ↓'' |structure (expanded) |Move focus across sub-rows. ↑ at topmost sub-row ''collapses'' and steps into the pill section above; ↓ at bottommost sub-row collapses and steps into the section below (or input). |
|''Esc'' |structure (expanded) |Collapse back to compact view (focus stays on strip) |
|''Esc'' |structure (compact) |Return focus to input |
|''Backspace / Delete'' |structure (focused axis pill) |Remove this axis from the channel's chain — re-renders the strip and the tree. |
|''Shift-← / Shift-→'' |structure (focused axis pill) |Reorder the focused axis within the chain. |
|''Enter'' |structure (focused axis pill) |Open the axis picker in ''replace'' mode — pick a different axis to swap into this position. |
|''Enter / Space'' |structure (focused `+` pill) |Open the axis picker in ''append'' mode — pick an axis to add to the end of the chain. |
|''← / →'' |leader |Move focus between leader pills (clamps at edges) |
|''Enter / Space'' |leader |Fire the focused leader — same actions as the typed-gesture path (key + idle). The strip re-renders for the new active view; focus returns to the strip if the leader stays visible. |
|''Esc'' |leader |Return focus to input |
|''↑'' |menu |Move selection up; at top-of-list, returns focus to input |
|''↓'' |menu |Move selection down |
|''→'' |menu |Drill into the selected item (push a new stage). On a tree container, descends children; on a ''leaf'' row carrying a non-empty entity type, opens the action-menu stage of that type. Tab does ''not'' drill — it cycles sections. |
|''←'' |menu |Pop one stage (back). No-op at root depth. Same effect as Esc-in-menu; Esc additionally refocuses input at root. |
|''Space'' on toggle |menu |Flip the bound value (palette stays open) |
|''Space'' on text/number/date |menu |Enter edit mode — bound value pushed into input, Enter commits, Esc cancels |
|''← / →'' on daterange |menu |Switch the active sub-date (start ↔ end). The active side is boxed/accented. |
|''+ / -'' on daterange |menu |Adjust the active sub-date by ±1 day. Shift = ±month, Ctrl = ±year. Fires the row's `ca-on-commit` after each change. |
|''Space / Enter'' on daterange |menu |Type the active sub-date via the smart parser (Enter commits, Esc cancels). |
|''↑ / ↓'' on daterange |menu |Normal menu navigation — ↑/↓ are NOT trapped, so you arrow straight down to the Save row. |
|''Space'' on any tiddler row |menu |If no kind-specific Space handler applies, scans applicable actions for the row's tiddler. Two paths run in parallel: catalogue (action `ca-entity-type` matches the row's bound type) and filter (action `ca-applies` filter non-empty with `<currentTiddler>` = row title). Union of matches opens the action-menu stage. Empty match → silent no-op. Works in catalogue and tree views, leaf and container rows. |
|''+ / -'' on number |menu |Adjust by `ca-step` (default 1). Shift = `ca-step-medium` (5). Ctrl = `ca-step-large` (20). Matched on physical key (Equal/NumpadAdd/Minus/NumpadSubtract) so layout is irrelevant. |
|''DEL / Backspace'' |menu |On an overridden setting → confirm drill to restore default. On a non-shadow tiddler in a diagnostic list → confirm drill to delete. On a synthetic row declaring `ca-on-delete` → fires that action (confirm-wrapped iff `ca-on-delete-consequence` is set). Otherwise no-op. |
|''Shift-DEL / Shift-Backspace'' |menu (root stage) |Add a ''hide-entry'' visibility pill for the selected row — the entry disappears from the root menu until the pill is removed. |
|''Ctrl-↑ / Ctrl-↓'' |menu |On a synthetic row declaring `ca-on-move-up` / `ca-on-move-down` → fires that action (typically swaps the row with its neighbour in the parent tiddler's JSON array). `stage.selectedIndex` is pre-bumped so selection follows the row. No action declared → falls through to bare ↑/↓ (selection nudge). |
|''← / →'' |details |Switch template tab when multiple templates apply |
|''↑ / ↓'' |details |Scroll the drawer natively |
|''Hold Ctrl'' |any |Open the detail drawer; release to hide. Always-on mode keeps it visible. Suppressed in edit mode. |
|''← / →'' |preview |Cycle between candidate previews when two or more apply — applies on landing (selecting IS navigating; no Enter/Space). No-op with a single candidate. |
|''Esc'' |preview |Return focus to the input. The pane stays visible — it's stack-attached, not focus-attached. |
|''↑ / ↓'' |preview |Native scroll inside the pane. |
|''Click'' on a result row |menu |Sets focus → selects → fires (Shift-click = keep open) |
|''Click'' on a filter / visibility pill |filter / visibility |Focus that pill (the × on the pill removes it) |
|''Click'' on a view pill |view |Activate that view |
|''Click'' on a preset pill |preset |Apply that preset |
|''Click'' on a leader pill |leader |Fire that leader (same as Enter / typed-gesture commit) |
|''Click'' on a breadcrumb segment | |Pop back to that stage |
|''Hover'' on any row | |Native browser tooltip shows the row's `ca-hint` text. |
|''Hover'' on a pill |filter / visibility / preset |Native browser tooltip shows the pill's hint. |

The hotkey is configured at `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open`.

! Tags

|!Tag |!Purpose |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry` |Root-stage menu item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` |Per-entity-type action menu item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action-provider` |Dynamic-action provider — contributes computed actions to a row's action menu. Fields: `ca-applies` (gating filter, `<currentTiddler>` = focused row) + `ca-provider-items` (filter returning one JSON action spec per result, same shape as `ca-items-from` rows). Lets one tiddler emit N actions derived from the focused entity (e.g. `rimir/kind`'s "Manage <ref>…" per reference field). Evaluated as a fifth path in `loadActionsForType`. |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/setting` |Setting toggle exposed under the engine's "Settings" entry |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/diagnostic` |Diagnostic item exposed under the engine's "Diagnostics" entry |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/configuration` |Aggregated under the engine's "Configuration" root entry (Settings, Diagnostics, etc.) |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/template` |Detail-pane template — wikitext rendered with `currentTiddler` bound to the picked item |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/filter` |Declarative ''filter'' — adds a removable pill whose expression is appended (intersected) to every result-list filter |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility` |Declarative ''visibility rule'' — adds a removable pill whose predicate filter hides matching root entries |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/view` |Declarative view — composition of one or more channels. Each view appears as a pill in the view strip |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/channel` |Declarative channel — `(roots, children, leaf, label)` + row decorations + optional `ca-channel-axes` chain. Referenced by view tiddlers via `ca-view-channels` |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/axis` |Declarative grouping axis — `(key, label, sort)` derive-key spec. Referenced by channels / views via `ca-channel-axes` / `ca-view-axes`. Buckets the channel's source set at the top of the descent, with the chain consuming one tree depth per axis. Authored in-palette via ''Manage axes'': a ''+ New axis…'' creator opens the raw `ca-axis-key` editor with a live ''✓ N matches'' count then names + saves the axis under `…/axes/`; each existing axis drills into a per-facet field editor (name / hint / icon / key / label / sort / sort-keys / empty-label / delete), while a shipped (shadow-only) axis offers ''clone to edit'' instead. Composed into a channel's chain from the Structure strip's axis pills. |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader` |Leader-key gesture — key + idle window fires a wikitext action chain |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/preset` |Saved `(view, filters, visibility)` bundle — surfaced as a pill in the preset strip |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/help` |In-palette help section — drillable via the ''Help'' entry or the `?` leader. Uses standard cascade-item fields (`ca-name`, `ca-icon`, `ca-group`, `ca-order`, `ca-hint`); body wikitext renders in the side preview |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview` |Side-preview candidate — auto-attached to the right-pane preview when `ca-preview-applies` matches the active context. The tagged tiddler IS the template by default (override via `ca-preview-template`). Fields: `ca-preview-applies` (filter), `ca-preview-name` (pill label), `ca-preview-title` (caption), `ca-preview-order` (sort). When two or more candidates apply at once, a pill row appears at the top of the pane — ←/→ when focus is on the preview cycles between them. |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/row-icon` |Row-icon registration — declares a small glyph that renders in a footer strip beneath any tiddler-bearing row whose `ca-row-icon-applies` filter matches (or, for the built-in `ca-row-icon-key: url`, whose URL field carries a value). Alt-↵ on the row (or clicking the glyph) fires the icon's `ca-row-icon-action` / `ca-row-icon-message`. Fields: `ca-row-icon-key`, `-glyph`, `-hint`, `-applies`, `-payload`, `-action`, `-message`, `-primary`, `-order`. |
|`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/lens` |Lens — a type-driven row decorator projecting one or more ''slots'' onto each data row: ''name'' (replace the display name), ''icon'' (leading glyph), ''annotation'' (trailing badge). Each slot is projected by a `ca-lens-<slot>-filter` (cheap — a filter evaluated per row with `<currentTiddler>` = row title; first non-empty result fills the slot) or `ca-lens-<slot>-template` (rich — wikitext rendered per visible row, windowed + cached; filter takes precedence when both are set). Per-slot single-select: the active lens per slot persists in `$:/state/rimir/cascade-palette/lens/<slot>`; a multi-slot lens appears in each slot's chooser. Fields: `ca-lens-name`, `-chip`, `-hint`, `-help`, `ca-lens-when` (applicability — empty result hides the lens; evaluated with no row context), `ca-lens-default` (space-separated slot names this lens seeds on first load), `ca-lens-<slot>-filter` / `-<slot>-template`, `ca-lens-actions` (`via-entity-type` to own the standard entity-type action bridge, or a filter returning action titles to surface on a row — always-on, gated only by `ca-lens-when`, never by slot selection), `ca-order`. Authored in-palette: ''Manage lenses'' lists every lens — each row drills into a per-facet field editor (name / when / default-slot toggles / per-slot filter + template / actions chooser / delete; a shipped lens offers ''clone to edit'' instead) — plus a ''+ New … lens…'' creator per slot; the per-slot ''➕ New…'' pill / ''e'' edit / ''DEL'' delete give the live-preview filter author. Supersedes the former row-label + structure-toggle subsystems. Ships generic ''Modified'' (filter) and ''Tags'' (template) annotation lenses; `rimir/kind` ships a ''Kind'' icon lens (which also owns the kind actions) showing each instance's `kind.icon`. |

! Fields

|!Field |!Type |!Where |!Purpose |
|`ca-name` |string |entry, action |Display name in the row |
|`ca-hint` |string |entry, action |Subtitle / right-aligned hint |
|`ca-icon` |string |entry, action |Single character or emoji prefix |
|`ca-order` |number |entry, action |Sort key (lower = higher in list, default 100) |
|`ca-kind` |`leaf`\|`drill`\|`toggle`\|`number`\|`text`\|`date`\|`daterange` |entry, action, setting |Leaf fires actions, drill pushes next stage, toggle flips a bound boolean, number adjusts via `+/-` (Space to type-set), text edits a string via Space → type → Enter, date adjusts via `+/-` ±day (Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year), Space → typed-edit with smart parser. `daterange` binds ''two'' date fields (`ca-bind-field` + `ca-bind-field-end`) in one row: ←/→ switch the active sub-date, +/- adjust it (Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year), Space/Enter type it; ↑/↓ are left for normal menu navigation (arrow down to Save). A fresh range is seeded from `ca-default-start` / `-end`. |
|`ca-actions` |wikitext |leaf items |Fired on Enter |
|`ca-confirm` |`yes`\|empty |leaf items |When `yes`, the leaf's actions are wrapped in a confirm-drill stage rather than fired directly. The consequence text shows the cost of confirming (e.g. "Delete tiddler X"). |
|`ca-confirm-consequence` |string |leaf with `ca-confirm:yes` |Text shown as the ''hint'' of the synthetic Confirm row (inline, always visible) AND in the detail drawer banner (Ctrl-hold or details-always-on). Supports `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>` substitution. |
|`ca-after-fire` |`close`\|`pop` |leaf |Post-fire behaviour. Default `close` (closes the palette). `pop` fires the action then pops one stage, keeping the palette open — for single-select sub-drills inside a field-edit flow, so the user lands back on the field stage with their pick already applied. |
|`ca-entity-type` |string\|`*` |action |Catalogue-path binding. The action surfaces on rows whose emitting channel declared `ca-channel-row-entity-type` matching this value. Use `*` for a global. Tree-view rows have no bound entityType — use `ca-applies` for those. |
|`ca-applies` |filter |action |Filter-path discovery. Evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the row's title; non-empty result ⇒ action surfaces on that row in ''any'' view (catalogue or tree). Combines with `ca-entity-type` (union, deduplicated by action title). |
|''(auto-derive)'' |//config// |action |When the wiki sets `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/entity-type-field` to a field name, an action's `ca-entity-type: <X>` ALSO matches any row whose tiddler carries `<configured-field>: <X>`. Lets catalogue plugins surface their actions in tree / flat views without authoring per-action `ca-applies`. The cascade-palette engine ships no default — typically set by a type-system plugin (e.g. `rimir/kind` ≥ 0.1.50 ships it as `kind.type`). Empty / missing config = no auto-derive. |
|`ca-default` |`yes`\|empty |action |Marks the "Enter on entity result" default action |
|`ca-action-when` |filter |action |Refinement filter — narrows whichever path matched (entity-type or `ca-applies`) by per-row state. Evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the picked entity. Non-empty result ⇒ action is applicable; empty/missing filter ⇒ always applicable. Used to hide actions that don't make sense for a specific tiddler (e.g. "Mark done" only when `done` field is empty). |
|`ca-next-scope` |filter |drill items |Filter expression for the new stage's items (mutually exclusive with `ca-items-from`) |
|`ca-items-from` |filter |drill items |Filter that returns one JSON-encoded item shape per result. The palette parses each as a synthetic cascade item (no backing tiddler). Use for stages populated from configuration data rather than tiddlers. Mutually exclusive with `ca-next-scope`. |
|`ca-sort-rows` |`name`\|empty |drill (items-from) |Opt the synthetic `ca-items-from` rows into data-row sorting: currently-selected rows float to the top (a `toggle` whose bound field holds its `ca-true-value`, or any row marked `ca-selected: yes`), then the rest sort alphanumerically by their displayed (lensed) name, within each `ca-order` group. Plain `ca-next-scope` (tiddler-title) stages sort unconditionally; structured items-from menus omit this to keep their authored layout. Used by `rimir/kind`'s ref / enum pickers. |
|`ca-selected` |`yes`\|empty |items-from row |Marks a non-toggle row (e.g. a single-select `leaf`) as the current selection so `ca-sort-rows` floats it to the top — the engine can read a toggle's on-state from its binding, but a leaf carries no bind state. |
|`ca-next-title` |string |drill items |Title shown in breadcrumb for the new stage |
|`ca-next-entity-type` |string |drill items |Sets the next stage's entity type (enables action-menu drilling on Right/Space) |
|`ca-next-default-action` |wikitext |drill items |Fired on Enter in the next stage when no entity default exists |
|`ca-next-as-link` |`yes`\|empty |drill items |When `yes`, the next-stage filter results render as plain link rows (no chevron, Enter navigates) even if the result tiddlers carry `ca-kind`. Use for inspector / diagnostic lists. |
|`ca-group` |string |entry, action |Override the visual cluster label. Defaults to the contributing plugin's `name`. Headers are suppressed when only one cluster is present in a stage. |
|`ca-visibility-filter` |filter |entry |If present and returns no results, the entry is hidden from the root menu |
|`ca-bind-tiddler` |string |toggle, number, text, date, drill |Target tiddler holding the bound value. On a `drill` (e.g. a single/multi-select picker sub-drill) this is purely informational — the palette renders the current bound value on the right of the row so the user sees their pick. |
|`ca-bind-field` |string |toggle, number, text, date, daterange, drill |Target field (default `text`). Same dual role as `ca-bind-tiddler` on drills. On a `daterange` this is the ''start'' date field. |
|`ca-bind-field-end` |string |daterange |The ''end'' date field of a range row (on the same `ca-bind-tiddler`). Falls back to `ca-bind-field` if unset. |
|`ca-default-start` / `ca-default-end` |smart-date expr |daterange |Seed values for a ''fresh'' range (both fields empty) on stage entry — never overwrite existing values. Accepts the smart-date forms (`+2w`, `today`, `tomorrow`, `2026-07-01`, `01.07.2026`). |
|`ca-bind-path` |string |toggle, number, text, date |Optional comma-separated walk inside the JSON-decoded field text (e.g. `prefs,layout`). Omit to bind the whole field. |
|`ca-bind-type` |scribetype name |toggle, number, text, date |Scribetype handler used for value round-trip (default `text/plain`). `application/x-string-array` enables list-membership semantics on toggle; a whole-field bind stores a TW titlelist (entries with spaces wrapped in `[[…]]`), while a sub-path bind (`ca-bind-path`) stores the array inside the host JSON document. `application/x-tw-date` / `application/x-tw-datetime` round-trip date kinds (the latter is the default for date kinds when unset). Requires `rimir/scribe`. |
|`ca-true-value` |string |toggle |Value written for "on" state (default `yes`). For `string-array` binds, this is the list element added/removed by the toggle. |
|`ca-false-value` |string |toggle |Value written for "off" state (default `no`). Ignored for string-array binds (the toggle removes `ca-true-value` from the list instead). |
|`ca-min` |number |number |Lower clamp. Together with `ca-max` triggers the inline slider render. |
|`ca-max` |number |number |Upper clamp. |
|`ca-step` |number |number |Step for bare `+/-` (default 1) |
|`ca-step-medium` |number |number |Step for Shift-`+/-` (default 5) |
|`ca-step-large` |number |number |Step for Ctrl-`+/-` (default 20) |
|`ca-step-day` / `-month` / `-year` |number |date, daterange |Step for bare/Shift/Ctrl `+/-` (and ↑/↓) respectively on a date row (each defaults to 1) |
|`ca-date-format` |TW format-date string |date, daterange |Display format for the row value. Default `DD.MM.YYYY`. Examples: `YYYY-0MM-0DD` (ISO), `DDth MMM YYYY` (long). |
|`ca-default-value` |number |number |Value used when the bound field is empty / unparseable |
|`ca-help` |string (multiline) |entry, action, setting |Longer-form help text shown in the detail drawer. Falls back to `ca-hint` when absent. |
|`ca-on-delete` |wikitext |any row |Fired on DEL / Backspace. Receives `<<picked>>` + standard stage substitution. Takes priority over the built-in restore-default / delete-tiddler paths. Used by synthetic JSON-array rows whose "delete" means mutating the parent tiddler. |
|`ca-on-delete-consequence` |string |row with `ca-on-delete` |Optional. If set, DEL pushes a confirm-stage with this consequence text instead of firing immediately. |
|`ca-on-move-up` / `ca-on-move-down` |wikitext |any row |Fired on Ctrl-↑ / Ctrl-↓. Symmetric with `ca-on-delete` for reorder semantics on synthetic JSON-array rows. cp pre-bumps `stage.selectedIndex` by ±1 so the selection follows the row through the change-hook's stage recompute. The action is responsible for boundary no-ops. |
|`ca-on-commit` |wikitext |text, number, date, daterange |Fired after a successful edit-mode commit with `<<picked>>` bound to the committed value. On a `daterange`, fired after every nudge / type-commit with `<<picked>>` = the current ''start'' date (read the end field off the bound tiddler). Works with or without `ca-bind-tiddler` (bind-less rows are pure value captures). |
|`ca-preview-template` |tiddler-title |entry, action |Title of a wikitext tiddler whose body renders in the right-pane ''preview'' when the user drills into this row. Pane stays visible while the registering stage (or any deeper one) is on the stack. Optional — omit to use ''tag-only opt-in'': set `ca-preview-per-row: yes` or `ca-preview-context` to enable the pane and let tagged side-preview tiddlers ([[side-preview tag|$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview]]) auto-attach the candidates. |
|`ca-preview-context` |filter |entry, action |Evaluated at drill-time in the parent stage's substitution scope (`<<picked>>`, `<<parent-picked>>`, etc.). First result becomes `<<currentTiddler>>` inside the preview template AND is exposed to deeper stages as `<<stage-preview-context>>`. Defaults to `<<picked>>` (the row being drilled into). |
|`ca-preview-title` |string |entry, action |Optional caption shown in the colored title strip above the preview body. Empty value hides the strip. |
|`ca-preview-name` |string |entry, action |Optional short label for the menu candidate's pill (when multiple candidates apply at once and the pill row is visible). Default = derived from the template title's last path segment. |
|`ca-preview-per-row` |`yes`\|`no` |entry, action |When `yes`, the preview pane re-resolves its context to the title of the currently-selected row on every selection change — i.e. ↑/↓ inside the drill stage updates the preview live, not just the initial drill. Used by browse-list drills where each row is a distinct document. Inherits into sub-drills (with the context locked to the drilled-into row, NOT the sub-drill's selected row — so action-menu sub-stages keep previewing the acted-upon entity). Default `no`. |
|`ca-preview-applies` |filter |side-preview tiddler |Evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the active context (row title or stamped). Returns non-empty → this side-preview becomes a candidate pill on the pane. Empty / missing = always applies. |
|`ca-preview-order` |number |side-preview tiddler |Sort key among tag-based candidates. Default `100`. Per-menu (`ca-preview-template` on an entry/action) is always candidate ''0'' regardless. |
|`ca-template-applies` |filter |template |Evaluated with `currentTiddler` bound to the picked item; template applies if filter returns the picked title. Omit for a universal template. |
|`ca-template-name` |string |template |Display name on the template tab (when multiple templates apply). |
|`ca-filter-name` |string |filter |Display name. Required. |
|`ca-filter-prefix` |string |filter |Input-prefix that triggers the filter (e.g. `/`, `prefix:`). Optional. Matched greedy-by-length, across both filter and visibility tag families. |
|`ca-filter-arg` |`text`\|`tag`\|`tiddler`\|`none` |filter |How the trailing input is interpreted. Default `text`. |
|`ca-filter-expr` |filter snippet |filter |Appended (intersected) with every producer's base filter — applied ''globally'' across all views (flat, tree, axis-bucketed). Virtual menu entries (tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`) are ''exempted'' from the narrowing by default; to narrow them too, type the query into the input bar. ''In tree-container views'' (channels with `ca-view-children` / `ca-channel-children` and no axis chain) ancestors of filter-matches are revealed so matches remain reachable via drill-down; revealed-only ancestors render dimmed (CSS class `rcp-row-ancestor-only`). Use `<arg>` as the argument operand placeholder; engine substitutes `[<arg>]` at pill-push time. |
|`ca-filter-chip` |string template |filter |Plain-text pill label. Use `<<arg>>` for substitution. Defaults to `ca-filter-name`. |
|`ca-filter-hint` / `-help` |string |filter |Hover / details-pane help. |
|`ca-reach-name` |string |reach |Display name. Required. |
|`ca-reach-mode` |`here`\|`everywhere` |reach |Search scope when this pill is active. `here` walks the subtree under the current stage; `everywhere` walks from the active view's root. Reach pills are mutually exclusive — pushing one evicts the other. |
|`ca-reach-chip` |string |reach |Plain-text pill label. Defaults to `ca-reach-name`. |
|`ca-reach-hint` / `-help` |string |reach |Hover tooltip / details-pane help. |
|`ca-meta-key` |meta key |search-meta |The cascade-item property this Meta pill exposes (`name`, `hint`, or any author-defined key). Matcher reads `item[<key>]` only. |
|`ca-tiddler-field` |tiddler field name |search-field |The tiddler field this Field pill exposes (`text`, `caption`, `tags`, or any field of the row's backing tiddler). Matcher reads `wiki.getTiddler(item.title).fields[<name>]` only. |
|`ca-chip` |string |search-meta, search-field |Plain-text pill label. Defaults to the key/field name. |
|`ca-hint` / `ca-help` |string |search-meta, search-field |Hover tooltip / details-pane help. |
|`ca-search-fields` |space-separated meta keys |entry, action, item |Which cascade-item meta keys the matcher walks for THIS row when no Meta pill is pushed. Default per global config `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/search-fields-default` (ships `name hint`). |
|`ca-search-skip` |`yes` |entry, action, item |When `yes`, the deep walker excludes this row from results AND does not descend its subtree. Default auto-skip for `text` / `number` / `date` / `daterange` / `toggle` / `confirm` row kinds. |
|`ca-visibility-name` |string |visibility |Display name. Required. |
|`ca-visibility-prefix` |string |visibility |Input-prefix (e.g. `hide:`). Optional. |
|`ca-visibility-arg` |`text`\|`tag`\|`tiddler`\|`none` |visibility |How the trailing input is interpreted. Default `text`. |
|`ca-visibility-expr` |filter snippet |visibility |Predicate evaluated per root entry with `<currentTiddler>` bound to its title — non-empty result hides the entry. Use `<arg>` for the operand placeholder. |
|`ca-visibility-chip` / `-hint` / `-help` |string |visibility |Same shape as the filter equivalents. |
|`ca-view-name` |string |view |Display name on the view-strip pill and as the root breadcrumb segment |
|`ca-view-hint` |string |view |Tooltip on hover; appears in the detail pane when the view pill is focused |
|`ca-view-default` |`yes`\|empty |view |One view declares `yes` to be the initial selection on page load |
|`ca-view-channels` |space-separated titles |view |List of channel tiddler titles composing this view. When set, the view is multi-channel and the view-level structure fields are ignored. When unset, the engine wraps the view's own `ca-view-roots` / `ca-view-children` / etc. into a single implicit channel (back-compat). |
|`ca-view-include-entries` |`yes`\|`no`\|`auto` |view |Whether the built-in entries channel is appended. Default `auto` — appended iff at least one declared channel is tree-shaped. `yes` always appends, `no` never. |
|`ca-view-grouping` |`yes`\|`no` |view |Whether result rows cluster under section headers. Default `yes`. Replaces the deprecated global `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/grouping-enabled` toggle removed in 0.0.38 — grouping is structural intent of the view (e.g. multi-channel composition wants section headers; a strict flat list might not), so the view author owns the decision. |
