|`ca-view-lens-name` / `-icon` / `-annotation` |lens title |view |The view's DEFAULT row-decoration lens per slot (Name / Icon / Note). Inherited by every channel unless the channel overrides it. Empty = slot off by default. These are the relocated global lens choosers — edited from the VIEW row of the Structure strip. |
|`ca-channel-lens-name` / `-icon` / `-annotation` |lens title |channel |Per-channel OVERRIDE of the view's default lens for that slot. Empty = inherit the view default. Edited from the channel's row in the Structure strip (shows "(inherit view)" when inheriting). The same tiddler appearing in two channels can therefore decorate differently. |
|`ca-view-locked` |space-separated slot names |view |Slots the view LOCKS (`name` / `icon` / `annotation`): a locked slot forces the view's default lens onto every channel, ignoring channel overrides. Toggled with `l` on a VIEW lens pill in the Structure strip. |
