|`ca-view-show-side-preview` |`yes`\|`no` |view |Auto-open the side-preview pane on rows whose title matches any tag-registered preview's `ca-preview-applies` filter (tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview`), OR whose row carries its own `ca-preview-template` (e.g. Overview rows). Default `yes`. Set to `no` on views where the pane would be noisy / unwanted (e.g. pure structural browsers); this also suppresses Overview-row previews. Pane stays hidden when no candidate matches — no placeholder. Per-menu (`ca-preview-template` on an entry/action) and explicit opt-in (`ca-preview-per-row: yes`) are unaffected by this flag. |
|`ca-view-preview` |tiddler title |view |Like `ca-channel-preview` but at view scope: emits one synthetic ''Overview'' row (grouped under the view name) leading the result list at the root stage. Focusing it renders the template; ''Enter'' moves focus into the preview pane. |
