|`ca-position-<view-slug>` |string |entry |Per-view position override. Slug is the view tiddler's basename. Same value space as `ca-position` |
|`ca-view-pick-mode` |`yes`\|empty |view |When `yes`, Enter on any row commits the row's effective path as a filter arg and returns to the prior view. Right-arrow still drills. |
|`ca-view-context-aware` |`yes`\|empty |view |When `yes` AND the sticky context strip is non-empty, the view pill paints a small indigo badge. Signals "this view will specialize for the pinned set" — the actual narrowing happens in channel/filter expressions that reference `<<sticky-context-list>>`. Purely a visual cue; the engine does not auto-narrow anything. |
|`ca-lens-<slot>-filter` |filter |lens |Per-row projection for ''<slot>'' (`name` / `icon` / `annotation`) — evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the row's backing tiddler title; the first non-empty result fills the slot, on data rows only (view-built rows and ca-next-scope items; command rows are exempt — palette entries / actions keep their explicit `ca-name`, whether they came from the entries channel or were surfaced by a roots filter over entry-tagged tiddlers, e.g. the ''Entries'' view). Empty result → slot falls back (intrinsic name / no glyph). |
