|`ca-preset-view` |view-title |preset |View active at save time. |
|`ca-preset-constraints` |JSON |preset |Object `{"filters": [{title, arg}, …], "visibility": [{title, arg}, …]}` — both lists at save time. |

! Shipped views (concrete shapes)

The built-in views compose channels as follows:

|!View |!Channels |!Notes |
|`entries` |implicit single channel (`roots: [tag[…/entry]]`); built-in entries channel not appended (auto, flat) |Default view; surfaces all plugin-declared entry tiddlers |
|`all-tiddlers` |implicit single channel (`roots: [!is[system]]`); built-in entries channel not appended (auto, flat) |Flat list of user tiddlers; row-actions navigate |
|`by-namespace` |implicit single channel (`roots: [!is[system]cp-child-of[]]`, `children: [!is[system]cp-child-of<currentTiddler>]`); built-in entries channel auto-appended |Path-segment tree via the plugin's `cp-child-of` filter operator |
|`by-parent` |implicit single channel (`roots: [tag[TableOfContents]]`, `children: [tag<currentTiddler>]`); built-in entries channel auto-appended |TW tag-tree |
|`by-namespace-pick` |same as `by-namespace` plus `ca-view-pick-mode: yes` |Hidden pick variant — Enter commits picked tiddler as filter arg |
|`hybrid` |two explicit channels (`channels/tag-tree` + `channels/path-tree`) plus built-in entries channel |Demo view exercising multi-channel composition. Rows from each channel interleave by sort; the channel name becomes the default `ca-group` per row |
|`by-date` |implicit single channel (`roots: [!is[system]!is[shadow]]`); chain `[by-year-created, by-month-created, by-day-created]` |Demo view exercising the axis chain. Pure grouping — no `children`, so day buckets contain tiddler leaves directly. |

The `cp-child-of` filter operator is shipped by this plugin (`widgets/cp-filter-ops.js`). Its operand is the parent tiddler title; with an empty operand it returns titles that contain no `/`. Authors writing custom path-style views can reuse it directly.

! Filter operators

The plugin ships four filter operators authors can reuse from any wikitext. All are pure, side-effect-free, and self-emit their source feed (no upstream `source` required unless noted).

|!Operator |!Operand |!Source |!Emits |
|`cp-child-of[<parent>]` |Parent tiddler title (empty → root level) |Ignored |Direct path-segment children of `<parent>` (titles whose prefix is `<parent>/` and whose remainder contains no further `/`). With an empty operand, titles that have no `/` at all. |
|`cp-actions-for[<entity-type>]` |Entity-type name (empty / `*` → globals only) |Ignored |Action titles (`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action`, drafts excluded) whose `ca-entity-type` matches the operand OR is `*`. Mirrors the catalogue + globals branches of `loadActionsForType`. |
|`cp-actions-applying-to[<title>]` |Target tiddler title (empty → no results) |Ignored |Action titles whose `ca-applies` filter returns non-empty with `currentTiddler` bound to the operand. Skips actions without `ca-applies` and actions whose `ca-applies` is blank. Mirrors `actionAppliesViaFilter`. |
|`cp-position-of[<view-slug>]` |View slug (empty → resolves base `ca-position` only) |Per-title input feed |For each input entry title, emits its effective tree-position parents in the named view. Resolution chain: `ca-position-<slug>` → `ca-position` → `at-root`. A blank slug field falls back to `ca-position`; `"none"` excludes the entry from that view. Multi-value via colon / newline split. |

These operators are reusable from any wikitext — kind-style "N actions" badges, namespace navigators, view diagnostics, etc.

! Macros

`$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/macros` (tagged `$:/tags/Macro`, imported by the palette's startup `\import` pragma) ships author-friendly wrappers:

|!Macro |!Equivalent filter |
|`cp.label(node)` |`[<node>get[caption]!is[blank]] :else[<node>get[ca-name]!is[blank]] :else[<node>]` — standard label fallback chain |
|`cp.actions-applying-to(title)` |`[cp-actions-applying-to<title>]` — friendlier alias |
|`cp.action-applies(entity-type)` |`[cp-actions-for<entity-type>]` — friendlier alias |
|`cp.position-of(view-slug)` |`[<currentTiddler>cp-position-of<view-slug>]` — defaults to `currentTiddler` |

A behavioural note for `by-namespace`: tree nodes are tiddlers, not derived path segments. If `foo/bar/baz` exists but no tiddler `foo` or `foo/bar` is present, those intermediate segments do not appear as drillable folders — create real tiddlers (even with empty body) at the parent paths to make them navigable.

! Entity-type drill on tree-view rows

The action menu for a typed row is reachable via two keys:

* ''Right-arrow'' on a ''leaf'' with a non-empty entity type — same gesture as the drill-into-instance flow inside `ca-next-scope` stages.
* ''Space'' on ''any'' typed row (leaf ''or'' container) — generalised action trigger. On containers, Right-arrow keeps its "descend into children" semantic, so Space is the only key that opens actions for a folder-style node.

Space also keeps its existing per-kind bindings (toggle / text / number / date edit) — those win when the row matches one of those kinds. Entity-type firing only applies when no kind-specific Space handler claims the keystroke.

The entity type is computed per row by the row's emitting channel:

* `ca-channel-row-entity-type` filter on a channel tiddler, OR
* `ca-view-row-entity-type` filter on an implicit-channel view

Both are evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the row's title. A non-empty first result is the entity type. Actions tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action` with `ca-entity-type` matching that type (or `*` for global) populate the action menu.

!! Filter-based action applicability

An action may further gate itself per entity instance by declaring `ca-action-when` — a filter evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the picked entity. A non-empty result means the action is applicable; empty / missing filter means always applicable (the default, back-compat with pre-0.0.39 actions).

Typical patterns:
* `[<currentTiddler>!has[done]]` — "Mark done" only shows for tiddlers without a `done` field
* `[<currentTiddler>!is[system]]` — "Delete" only on user tiddlers
* `[<currentTiddler>tags[]match[project]]` — domain-specific action only on tagged tiddlers

The applicability filter runs both when the action menu opens (deciding which actions to show) and when the per-row action-preview badge is computed (counting applicable actions for each visible typed row).

!! Per-row action preview

When a tree-view row carries a resolved entity type, the renderer shows a small `→N` badge next to the row name, where `N` is the count of actions that would appear if the user pressed Space on the row (or Right-arrow on a leaf). The count is computed by running the action loader (entity-type match + `ca-action-when` evaluation) for each visible row, including containers (which can't be reached via Right-arrow since that descends — Space is the action trigger on those).

The count is memoized by `(entity-type, row-title)` within a single render pass — keystroke-driven recomputations that just narrow the visible result list hit the cache. Per-view opt-out: set `ca-view-show-action-preview: no`. Stage / wiki changes invalidate the cache.

!! Perf footer (diagnostic)

When `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/show-perf-footer` is `yes`, a small footer renders below the hint row with the latest:

* `recompute` — milliseconds for `recomputeStage` (filter evaluation + sort)
* `render` — milliseconds for `renderStage` (DOM construction)
* `items / results` — pre/post query-filter row counts
* `actions Xms (N rows)` — total action-preview evaluation time + how many rows were preview-evaluated (only shown when non-zero)

Use it to spot slow filters (large `recompute`), expensive views with many rows, or to gauge the cost of per-row action preview before disabling it on a view.

! Shipped axes

The plugin ships five axes for the common cases. All live under `$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/axes/`.

|!Axis |!Key |!Sort |!Notes |
|`by-year-created` |`[get[created]format:date[YYYY]]` |`desc` |Newest year first. Pair with month + day for journaling-style trees. |
|`by-month-created` |`[get[created]format:date[MMM]]` |`enum` |Jan…Dec via `ca-axis-sort-keys`. |
|`by-day-created` |`[get[created]format:date[0DD]]` |`asc` |Zero-padded so alphabetical sort = chronological. |
|`by-year-modified` |`[get[modified]format:date[YYYY]]` |`desc` |Same shape as the created variant. |
|`by-field` |`[get<axis-param-field>]` |`asc` |''Parametric.'' Set the `field` param when adding the axis via the picker (default empty — placeholder for user to fill in). |

''Session state for an axis chain'' lives at `$:/state/rimir/cascade-palette/channel-axes/<slug>` where `<slug>` is the channel title's last `/`-segment (or, for implicit channels, the view title's last segment). Body: JSON `{"axes":[{"title":"…","params":{…}}, …]}`. Delete the tiddler to revert a channel to its declared `ca-channel-axes` default.

